				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Pros:
<br />
Buff duration timers get frozen when the pet is suspended.
<br />
Pre-Buff a pet and pull it out for the strike target.
<br />
Ability to invis up, move and not lose your pet.
<br />
Backup pet, if the first one dies.
<br />
Supended pets act if you did not have a pet in the first place.
<br />
Skill has unlimited usage, with no re-cycle time limitations.
<br />

<br />
Cons:
<br />
Pets do not retain grow/shrink size when un-suspended.
<br />
Pets do not retain taunt/don't taunt flag when un-suspended.
<br />
There is a 2 or 3 second cast to to suspend and un-suspend pets and you can be interupted.
<br />
There is a range limit on supending your pet.  At a certain distance, it stops working.
<br />
If your pet is agro or your pet is on any NPC's agro list, they can not be suspended.
<br />

<br />
The first rank cost 5aa and the second rank cost 3aa.
<br />
The biggest use I've gained from this skill was the ability to have a pet ready for bosses.  Raid leaders normaly don't like pets to be up on the way to the ubers for reason from pets causing mob positioning problems, breaking mezz, and lag ect...<br />_________________<br /><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=450587>Maujin Buu</a>: 65 Feral Lord - Prexus
<br />
<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=450605>Gramz Thull</a>: 61 Warlord - Prexus (retired)
<br />
<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=450498>Feelx Junglevibe</a>: 61 Hierophant - Prexus (taxi)</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
